parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Takata airbag inflator can cause the airbag to deploy incorrectly, leading to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag light turns on sporadically
the airbag warning chime sounds
the airbag light stays on for a few seconds and then turns off
the airbag light comes on when the car is backed out of the garage or driven forward.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of replacement parts for the Takata airbag inflator recall can cause delays in the repair process, leaving vehicles on the road with potentially faulty airbags.
symptoms: The part for the recall repair is unavailable
the manufacturer exceeds a reasonable amount of time for the recall repair
the contact is unable to get the repair completed due to lack of available dealers to service the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Slow Remedy for Airbag Recall and Repair
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The slow response to the Takata airbag inflator recall can cause delays in the repair process, leaving vehicles on the road with potentially faulty airbags.
symptoms: The contact receives notification of the recall but is unable to get the repair completed due to lack of available parts or dealers
the manufacturer takes too long to replace the faulty airbag inflator.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Direct Ignition Cassette Unit can cause the vehicle to shut down suddenly, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving on highways.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts down suddenly
the engine stalls
the car automatically shuts down
the part melts or burns out
the car experiences repeated shutdowns.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and shut down can cause the vehicle to lose power and control, leading to accidents, especially when driving on highways.
symptoms: The engine stalls
the vehicle shuts down suddenly
the car loses power
the car is unable to restart
the car experiences repeated shutdowns.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Exhaust Manifold/Catalytic Converter can cause the vehicle to experience reduced performance, decreased fuel efficiency, and increased emissions, which can lead to environmental and health hazards.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences reduced performance
decreased fuel efficiency
increased emissions
the part needs to be replaced
the part is on back order.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause a loss of braking power, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle takes longer to stop than usual
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal travels further than usual before the brakes engage
the vehicle pulls to one side when braking
the rear brake rotors show excessive wear
the vehicle is unstable during emergency braking maneuvers
brake dust accumulates rapidly on the rear wheels.
